4.  ACCOUNTS AND RECRUITMENT PROCESS
4.1 Registration
To be registered as a Talent for sending and receiving work offers in the Platform. The Talent shall first create an account through tod-Z’s Platform; however, the approval of the Talent’s Account is subject to passing the recruitment process by tod-Z and its Third Party services providers.
4.2 Recruitment Process
-   After the Talentcreates an Account, such an Account shall be subject to profile screening,
-   If the Talent passes the profile screening, they will be invited to do an aptitude/cognitive test,
-   Upon passing these tests, the Talents will be invited to take a technical test assessment,
-   Consequently, a live web interview will take place for final assessment of the Talents.
In case the Talent passed all required assessments and tests by tod-Z. the Talent will be assigned their hourly rate by tod-Z as per section 4.1, if the Talent approves the rates they accordingly will have a profile created on the Platform to apply to the Projects offered by Clients in tod-Z under the regulations made in these Terms and Conditions.
In the event that the Talent fails in any of the abovementioned steps, they can re-apply with tod-Z after 3 months from the previous registration.
4.3 Sending offers to Clients
After the Talent’s registration to create an account to access our marketplace has been approved by us, the Talent will be able to communicate anonymously (as per section 4.6) with the Client, receive requests and respond to Client’s requests in the Platform by sending an offer to the Client stating the exact hours and days needed to complete the potential Project.
The Talent shall respond  to the Client’s request by sending the offers  to the Client within 5 working days, in case the Talent did not answer the request within the determined days, the Client’s request to the Talent will be withdrawn automatically.
Once the Client accept the Talent’s offer, the Client and Talent agree that they will communicate anonymously and exclusively through our Platform during sending the requests, hiring process and all the duration of the Project until completion.
4.4 Extension of Project’s Duration
In the event that the Client or the Talent needs to extend the Project’s period for any reason, they shall communicate it to the other User and it shall be approved by both Users in order to extend the Project’s duration in the Platform.
4.5 Talents Hourly Rates
Upon passing all assessments and tests carried out by tod-Z and their Third Parties service providers. Thus, tod-Z evaluate and asses the hourly rate that shall be assigned to the Talent. The hourly rate assessment is subject to the Talent’s skills, experience, and assessments scores as per our Anti-Bias and Anti-Discrimination approach for hiring Talents and not based on gender, nationality, or race.
4.6 Anonymity
tod-Z adopts an Anti-Bias and Anti-Discrimination approach for hiring Talents and assigning their hourly rates. As the assessment of Talents   and their hourly rate assignment are only based on their skills and qualifications. therefore, Users agree to maintain complete anonymity while working on Projects via tod-Z Platform.
